          D
          
            +
          
        
        A
      
    
    {\textstyle P=D^{+}A}
   is simply the transition matrix of a random walker on the graph, assuming non-negative weights. For example, let 
  
    
      
        
          e
          
            i
          
        
      
    
    {\textstyle e_{i}}
   denote the i-th standard basis vector. Then 
  
    
      
        x
        =
        
          e
          
            i
          
        
